items.name: Manju Warrier (Indian actress, dancer, singer and producer)
items.description:
By request of @Kavin_ak

This LyCORIS has been trained after carefully selecting 50 images. All photos have been enhanced to make the most of them.

Manju Warrier is an Indian actress, producer, classical dancer and playback singer who predominantly works in Malayalam cinema industry.

I don't ask for anything but any respectful constructive review that would be highly appreciated! Please press Like if you're happy with results after trying it out! Thanks in advance and enjoy it!

From my experience it runs best with ICBINP - "I Can't Believe It's Not Photography", Edge Of Realism, pirsusEpicRealism, epicDiffusion, RealisticVision, CyberRealistic, Deliberate checkpoints, among others, although I think it will be just fine in other SD 1.5 models as well.

CFG scale should be between 4-7.

LyCORIS weights should be between 1-1.4

Notice: This free work is intended for art and illustration purposes of emergent technology and not intended nor' trained for making illicit images, as the author I've taken care to not use any private data in the training process or designed it for such purposes. By downloading this model you are agreeing with the aforementioned intent and that you will not use my work to create / share images of a potentially immoral and / or illegal nature.

items.name: waterstylellm_XL
items.description:
This model tests a new marking method, which uses LLM to describe and mark images instead of traditional Deepbooru marking. Firstly, it can be clarified that LLM currently has hallucinations in image recognition, and there is currently no good solution.

recommand weight:0.8-1

prompt:waterstylellm,1girl,<lora:waterstylellmV1_SDXL_lora-000006:1.0>

Example 1Ôºö¬†waterstylellm, The image features a woman with long hair, wearing a shiny silver suit, and standing in a water-filled room. The woman's hair is flowing and appears to be wet, which suggests that she has just emerged from the water. The silver suit she is wearing adds a futuristic and metallic touch to her appearance, making her look like a cyborg or a robot. The water-filled room creates an interesting and visually appealing environment, with the woman standing out as the focal point of the scene.¬†¬†

Example 2Ôºöwaterstylellm, The image features a young woman standing in front of a city skyline, with a sunset in the background. She is wearing a white jacket and has long hair. The city skyline consists of tall buildings, and the sunset creates a beautiful and colorful backdrop for the scene. The woman appears to be standing on a pier or a dock, with water visible in the background. The overall composition of the image is visually appealing and captures a moment of serenity and beauty in the cityscape.¬†

¬†

You can see that there is a lot of nonsense mixed in the LLM, but the training effect is not very poor. You can compare it with another model of the same dataset that I trained through routine training. https://civitai.com/models/120521/watermiku¬†¬†

This is a makeup LORA, which is more suitable for use when generating Asian female characters. The effects that can be achieved are:

1. Whitening

  • helmet

  • magic

  • full armor

  • book

  • ascended (post-heresy / exile armor)

  • red armor (pre heresy)

WEAPONS

  • staff / polearm

BONUS

  • Rubric marines

items.name: Jamil - Granblue Fantasy
items.description:
Recommended weight: 0.7 to 0.95, depending on the model you're using. HiResFix(For A1111 users) or a second pass(for ComfyUI users) is recommended at higher weights. You won't need it for lower weights though.

Sometimes the lora will try to make him look much older than he is supposed to be. This can be fixed with a slight touch of the Age Slider embedding. Don't overdo it on that embedding, though. Also, I had some images here and there when the model tried to whitewash Jamil, which is not cool. Prompt Dark Skin if that is happening to you. And sometimes the model will try to dye his hair blue. Prompt brown hair to prevent that.

Jamil is here, and I hope you like it!

Some people have asked for this character in the comments for some of my other models, so here it is! He is pretty cool. My kind of character, yes. I hope you all enjoy it!

I haven't had a lot of time to work on AI art recently, the other elements of my life have been demanding a lot of time, but I'll slowly keep posting my stuff here as I get them done. Thank you for your patience!

I wonder how the new site layout will affect viewership for niche character models like the ones I make...

Who is Georgia?

Usage Notes

Georgia often has a nose ring in, and you'll sometimes see artifacts on her nose. You can put (nose ring:1.3) in the negative prompt to help deal with that.

Versions

Georgia was one of my earliest attempts at making a lora. In v3 I put together some of my learnings to improve it, but her eyes still weren't very accurate. With v4 locon, I applied a more refined understanding of the same strategies I used with v3, as well as improving the captions. It's also a locon rather than a lora, which essentially makes the file smaller while retaining the quality characteristics of a larger lora.

modelVersions.name: v4 locon

I found myself displeased with Georgia's eyes in previous versions of this lora. I applied some of the things I've learned since then, and created a superior version.

The v3 was an early revamp using a split weight strategy. But at that point I didn't have as clear a conception of what I wanted. Now I'm hitting a 2:1 primary to supporting ratio.

I also updated the captions. That didn't help with the artifacts her nose ring causes, however.

items.name: Adriana Chechik SDXL
items.description:
A LoRA for Adriana Chechik.

Process

  • Images (71)

    • Focus

      • 30 "full" body (waist/knees up)

      • 17 upper body (chest and head)

      • 18 close up (head and shoulders)

      • 6 weird angles/poses (range from "full" body to upper body)

    • Aspect ratio

      • 30 1:1

      • 41 3:4

    • Content (varied...)

      • faces (1 eyes closed, half smiling, 1 eyeglasses)

      • lighting

      • clothing

      • makeup

      • background

      • pose

    • Misc

      • I try to exclude any images that have a busy/complex scene/background. Abnormal clothing, hand gestures, etc. are cropped out when possible. My rule of thumb is that if I wouldn't want the image to be generated by the LoRA, I don't include it in the dataset. There are some exceptions to this rule, but it is a good starting point to trim the dataset.

      • As many duplicate clothing items, facial expressions, poses, pieces of jewelry, etc. are excluded as possible, but it can often be hard to avoid this.

      • Images are cropped by hand and left at whatever # of pixels achieves the desired final image. They are kept to 3:4, 4:3, or 1:1 aspect ratios.

      • Many others have commented that 71 images is unnecessary, and that 20 or so will do. I prefer to be in the 40-80 range.

  • Captions

    • All begin with "adriana chechik, a photo of a woman..."

    • I describe the clothing, jewelry, lighting, pose, angle, background, facial expression, makeup, and any other information I do not want showing up in the LoRA gens (abnormal hair color, for example) in sentence form.

    • I do not describe things I do want to show up in the LoRA, like eye color, hair color, skin tone, body proportions, etc.

    • I have experimented with adding a fake word "ohwx" to the captions with varying results. I did not do so for this LoRA.

  • Training Params

    • model: DreamshaperXL

    • text_encoder_lr: 0.0004

    • unet_lr: 0.0004

    • learning_rate: 0.0004

    • network_dim: 256

    • network_alpha: 1

    • lr_scheduler: constant

    • optimizer_type: Adafactor

    • train_batch_size: 1

    • dataset repeats: 20

    • epochs: 10 (sometimes up to 12 if I have a highly varied dataset)

    • max_train_steps: 20 * 10 * # of images (so for this one, it was 20 * 10 * 71 = 14,200)

  • How is it so small?

    • After training is complete, I am left with a 1.7gb safetensors file. I use the kohya gui to resize the lora with a rank of 256. This spits out a ~18mb safetensors file that is nearly identical to the 1.7gb file in practice.

I'm sure I missed something here, so let me know if there's any other info that would be useful.

items.name: CanvasXL
items.description:
Ongoing Updates

  • (8/28): Apologies for the lack of updates; my life has been unexpectedly hectic as of late; v3 has been in the works though! I have been on the fence about uploading v2-fp16 as the quality seemed to drop a lot in the conversion, and I have not been able to give much time to testing.

  • (8/18): An experimental fp16 version of the v1 model has been uploaded. Initial testing seems to indicate that the results are at least comparable! I have had to travel unexpectedly this week and will be getting v2-fp16 uploaded soon.

    • If you can run the bfloat16 version, bfloat16 will probably perform better.

  • (8/14): A v2 checkpoint has been uploaded. Please read the "about this version" notes in the drop-down panel to the right.

CanvasXL: Unleash Your Creativity

Presenting CanvasXL, an SDXL v1 Dreambooth fine-tune project which aims to empower your creativity like never before! Trained on a dataset of thousands of highly aesthetic, artistic AI-generated images, CanvasXL sets out to bring your vision to life with unparalleled beauty and creativity within the open-source image generation space.

I have tried my best to summarize the model, my intentions with it, and my plans around it in the text below. I hope you enjoy the fruits of my labor and create some beautiful images! If you like and want to support my work, you are welcome to buy me a coffee.

Features, Specifications, and Notices:

  • Versatility: CanvasXL produces a wide array of subjects and represents novel concept combinations impressively across many contexts.

  • Resolutions: Trained on 44 different resolutions, with particular preferences for 1024x1024 and 704x1216 (mobile portrait-style). Some subjects will be replicated better on one resolution than the other, currently.

  • Model Type (Base vs Refiner): Currently, a fine-tune of the SDXL v1 base model is presented. This model can be used for txt2img and img2img, however I plan to fine-tune the refiner model as well, once I have the time to figure it out!

  • Convenient Use: A ComfyUI workflow.json is available for easy set up of the model, to help you get started. You can copy it from here.

  • Format: The model is currently presented in bfloat16 format. If anyone needs a fp16 version, please leave a comment and I will create it when I have the time!

  • Demo Images: The generation parameters for the images should be available. The prompts were directly copied from a selection of nice-looking images on a popular AI image generation site. The 20 demo images were cherry picked from a set of approximately 300 images, and are completely unedited.

  • Future Plans: I have amassed a dataset of ~30k well-tagged, good-quality images. I am currently pruning the dataset to increase the quality, cleaving about 60% of the total images. However, I have only made it through half of the total dataset, so the training set should expand and improve as I have the time to work through the set. As significant additions are made to the training set, new training runs will be performed on my local machine and uploaded.

  • Content Notice: The training dataset is entirely free of NSFW, nudity, violent, or otherwise potentially-highly objectionable imagery. As a result, this model should not be expected to be able to replicate such subjects well or even at all, as it is explicitly intended to produce non-objectionable imagery.

  • Usage Notice: Please be aware that you are solely responsible for any content that you create using this model. In addition, your use of this model implies that you accept an agreement to not use it to produce harassing, harmful, illegal, or otherwise highly-objectionable imagery.

Resolution Buckets:

CanvasXL's training encompasses various resolution buckets, ranging from (512, 1664) to (1792, 512). Due to variance across training runs, the general distribution is described:

  • bucket 0: resolution (512, 1664), count: low

  • bucket 1: resolution (512, 1728), count: low

modelVersions.name: CanvasXL-bfloat16-v002
modelVersions.description:
CanvasXL v2 Release Notes

Over the past week, I have performed a number of training experiments with the goal of producing an improved version of the model. Sadly, my initial, as-planned training run for v2 did not produce especially appealing results. However, an interesting model was produced during subsequent testing runs. This version is not a 1:1 upgrade from v1, however I feel that it has an interesting versatility, so I wanted to share the checkpoint.

This checkpoint has been trained on a much larger subset of my total collected dataset, and as a result it tends to combine subjects in more interesting and versatile ways. However, this presents the double-edged sword that it is less tuned towards defaulting to an appealing aesthetic. While I have not had time to experiment too much, mixing and matching v2 and v1 as txt2img and img2img may produce interesting results!

At this point I have three short-term goals planned for this project:

  • Produce FP16 versions of the checkpoints (priority 1)

  • Produce a fine-tune of the refiner model (priority 2)

  • Work towards a "best of both worlds" v3 (priority 3)

The priority has largely been set in consideration of how much time and effort is expected to be required to tackle each item. Expect fp16 versions in the next few days, updates on the refiner in the same time-frame, and with a little luck, a refiner release, and perhaps even a v3 by week's end. No promises though! I am hoping that I can tune v2 using a similar strategy to v1, to produce v3. :)

items.name: Amatsukaze Kai Ni (Kancolle)
items.description:
An experimental character LoRA of Amatsukaze from Kantai Collection.

Info

Training with 32 images
Followed the manual form [ [Guide] Make your own Loras, easy and free ],
You can access to this guide in Suggested Resources section.

Recommended set up

Sampler: Euler a, DPM family series
Sampling steps: 20 or 25+
CFG Scale: 7
CLIP Skip: 2
*Do not use [restore face] on anime character!*

LoRA Weighting: [1 - 0.9]

Baking Step:
0. Drafting (512 x 512 res to find your desired sketch)
1. Hires fix (txt2img: 768 x 768, 768 x 512, 512 x 768, or above res)
2. inpaint (img2img: refine some unwanted effect, [Euler a] with 50+ step)
3. Upscaling (img2img: res*2 with [ControlNet Tile] & Ultimate SD upscale)

Upscaler for [Step 1 - 3]: [R-ESRGAN 4x+ Anime6B, 4x-AnimeSharp, 4x-UltraSharp]
I always skip Step 0, 2 :P

Basic prompts

AmatsukazeKaiNiKC, (KaiNi) dress, (KaiNi) hat, hair tubes, (white) sailor collar, garter straps, (grey) neckerchief, (KaiNi) thighhighs, (white) gloves

Some additional tags that you may use for reference

-(sailor) dress, (long sleeves) dress, (black) dress, (brown) dress, (short) dress
-(red) thighhighs, (striped) thighhighs, striped
-(right-hand) glove, single glove

One Big Jill

This was a nightmare, i failed many many attempts, and had to completly change my workflow in blender to achieve better results and save precious time

i figured the hard way that one scene is BAD, like really fucking bad, so i developed a new way that will allow me to generate multiple light settings

albeit with a heavy price, working with over 8million verts in the viewport is really really not fun, the AI was having trouble working with her face

and not properly recognizing her hair which is very asymmetrical and i still didn't figure the fucking captioning system, the information online is vague

and it seens people are hiding it on purpose, some say to add what you want when captioning, others say exclude, but both methods are very inefective

but i learned a lot in the proccess, and made a friend https://talkai.info/chat/, he can answer everything i ask and this means my debugging is more precise and less of a 'wtf i do now?', this was the first time i used chatgpt and it was honestly fun lol

this model is simple, a Jill, a very big Jill

but ain't gonna lie, i'm salty as fuck right now with this captioning bullshit

ALSO READ THIS

Listen, i know you guys prefer nodes (node fetish), WebUI (website fetish), but i'm 100% a visual/art guy, i like GUI's, i've used simple GUI's since i played CS1.5 for the first time 19 years ago

but sadly the ONLY GUI available is currently NMKD GUI which is very very outdated (understatement), and the guy only got 4 contributions at his Github (but none of then is ACTIVE AAAAAA), so if you are a coder, please get in contact with him

Carice Anouk van Houten born 5 September 1976) is a Dutch actress and singer. Her first leading role in the television film Suzy Q (1999) won her the Golden Calf for Best Acting in a Television Drama; two years later, she won the Golden Calf for Best Actress for Miss Minoes (2001).

She gained widespread recognition for her performance in Black Book (2006), the most commercially successful Dutch film to date, for which she won her second Golden Calf for Best Actress, in addition to nominations from the Chicago Film Critics Association, the European Film Academy, and the Online Film Critics Society. She was nominated for a Saturn Award for Best Supporting Actress for Valkyrie (2008), and won her fourth and fifth Golden Calf Awards for Best Actress for The Happy Housewife (2010) and Black Butterflies (2011). Her other notable English-language performances include Repo Men (2010), Black Death (2010), and Brimstone (2016).

Van Houten received international recognition for her role as Melisandre on the HBO television series Game of Thrones (2012‚Äì2019), for which she received nominations for two Screen Actors Guild Awards for Outstanding Performance by an Ensemble in a Drama Series and a Primetime Emmy Award for Outstanding Guest Actress in a Drama Series.
